The paper deals with computational geometry and topology, specifically the problem of summarizing the topological features of a set of persistence diagrams. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and computational topology (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures for solving the problem, which could place it in the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of different metrics, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
